spec: concurrent_futures_extra69
version: ">=3.9"
backend: python_module(concurrent.futures)

docs: https://docs.python.org/3/library/concurrent.futures.html

provenance:
  derived_from:
    - "https://docs.python.org/3/library/concurrent.futures.html — Python concurrent.futures module documentation"
    - "Test vectors verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-10"
  not_derived_from:
    - "CPython source: Lib/concurrent/futures/_base.py"
    - "CPython source: Lib/concurrent/futures/process.py"
  notes:
    - "This spec extends concurrent_futures_extra68.zspec.zsdl."
    - "Prior specs covered: ThreadPoolExecutor/ProcessPoolExecutor/Future/Executor __name__/__module__/__qualname__, exception identity and bases, submit/map/shutdown __qualname__, class __dict__/__mro__/__all__ metadata, method qualname/name equality and length tables, __loader__/__spec__/__file__/__cached__ class names, __spec__ attributes, code object attribute chains, __defaults__/__kwdefaults__ class names, doc content, ThreadPoolExecutor/Future __init__ code object attributes, ThreadPoolExecutor MRO entry names."
    - "This spec covers (cfann69 namespace): wave 238 theme — concurrent.futures exception __name__ and Future state method code objects. NEW in extra69: InvalidStateError.__name__=='InvalidStateError'; InvalidStateError.__module__=='concurrent.futures._base'; InvalidStateError.__qualname__=='InvalidStateError'; BrokenExecutor.__name__=='BrokenExecutor'; BrokenExecutor.__module__=='concurrent.futures._base'; BrokenExecutor.__qualname__=='BrokenExecutor'; Future.result.__code__.co_name=='result'; Future.result.__code__.co_argcount==2 (self + timeout=None); Future.cancel.__code__.co_name=='cancel'; Future.cancel.__code__.co_argcount==1 (just self). Note: BrokenProcessPool is NOT directly accessible via the concurrent.futures namespace in Python 3.14; BrokenExecutor is the available base class."
    - "concurrent.futures.InvalidStateError.__name__ == 'InvalidStateError'. InvalidStateError is defined in concurrent/futures/_base.py; its __name__ is 'InvalidStateError'. Verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-10."
    - "concurrent.futures.InvalidStateError.__module__ == 'concurrent.futures._base'. InvalidStateError is defined in concurrent/futures/_base.py; its __module__ is 'concurrent.futures._base'. Verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-10."
    - "concurrent.futures.InvalidStateError.__qualname__ == 'InvalidStateError'. InvalidStateError is a top-level class in its module; its __qualname__ is 'InvalidStateError'. Verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-10."
    - "concurrent.futures.BrokenExecutor.__name__ == 'BrokenExecutor'. BrokenExecutor is defined in concurrent/futures/_base.py; its __name__ is 'BrokenExecutor'. Verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-10."
    - "concurrent.futures.BrokenExecutor.__module__ == 'concurrent.futures._base'. BrokenExecutor is defined in concurrent/futures/_base.py; its __module__ is 'concurrent.futures._base'. Verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-10."
    - "concurrent.futures.BrokenExecutor.__qualname__ == 'BrokenExecutor'. BrokenExecutor is a top-level class in its module; its __qualname__ is 'BrokenExecutor'. Verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-10."
    - "concurrent.futures.Future.result.__code__.co_name == 'result'. Future.result is a Python method defined in concurrent/futures/_base.py; its code object's co_name is 'result'. Verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-10."
    - "concurrent.futures.Future.result.__code__.co_argcount == 2. Future.result takes self + timeout=None; co_argcount is 2. Verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-10."
    - "concurrent.futures.Future.cancel.__code__.co_name == 'cancel'. Future.cancel is a Python method; its code object's co_name is 'cancel'. Verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-10."
    - "concurrent.futures.Future.cancel.__code__.co_argcount == 1. Future.cancel takes only self; co_argcount is 1. Verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-10."
    - "All expected values verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-10."
  created_at: "2026-04-10T00:00:00Z"

error_model: python_exceptions

